{"id":87803,"title":"Training critical care nurses in trauma care.","abstract":"Trauma is the commonest cause of death in people aged under 40 years. Despite review and debate, the quality of trauma training and care varies. This article examines the literature relating to trauma training in UK military and civilian environments to identify current practice and recommendations for training. It also discusses the British Association of Critical Care Nurses Military Region's one-dayraum trauma critical care skills workshop.","date":"2014-07-02","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24984371","annotations":[{"name":"Civilian","weight":0.657726,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civilian"},{"name":"Death","weight":0.61887,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death"},{"name":"Military","weight":0.562106,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Military"},{"name":"United Kingdom","weight":0.496564,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom"},{"name":"Nurse","weight":0.478911,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nurse"},{"name":"Literature","weight":0.307409,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Literature"},{"name":"Training","weight":0.290873,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Training"},{"name":"British Armed Forces","weight":0.201782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Armed_Forces"},{"name":"Trauma (medicine)","weight":0.185436,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trauma_(medicine)"},{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.122521,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"Debate","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Debate"},{"name":"List of causes of death by rate","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_causes_of_death_by_rate"},{"name":"Intensive-care medicine","weight":0.0157947,"wikipedia_arti